iral hepatitis types is most likely to be transmitted through shared intranasal drug equipment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hepatitis A","Hepatitis B","Hepatitis C","Hepatitis D","Hepatitis E"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis C\u003C/strong\u003E virus can be transmitted through sharing contaminated intranasal drug equipment. Shared straws or banknotes can cause micro-trauma to nasal mucosa, facilitating blood-borne virus transmission between users.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other viral hepatitis types have different primary transmission routes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis A\u003C/strong\u003E spreads via the faecal-oral route through contaminated food and water\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis B\u003C/strong\u003E transmits through blood, sexual contact and from parent to child during birth\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis D\u003C/strong\u003E only occurs as a co-infection or superinfection in people with Hepatitis B\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis E\u003C/strong\u003E spreads via the faecal-oral route, mainly through contaminated water\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile all blood-borne viruses pose some risk with intranasal drug use, Hepatitis C is the most commonly transmitted hepatitis virus through this route.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hepatitis C virus transmission occurs through blood-to-blood contact, including sharing contaminated intranasal drug equipment","Hepatitis A and E viruses spread via the faecal-oral route through contaminated food and water","Hepatitis B spreads through blood, sexual contact and vertical transmission"],"references":["Mehta P, Grant LM, Reddivari AKR. Viral Hepatitis. 2024 Mar 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32119436","Lok 